summary: This is an FBI FD-192 form documenting property seized from Jeffrey Epstein's Palm Beach residence at 345 South County Road on August 28, 2006. The inventory lists numerous items including massage tables, photos, videos, CDs, message books, and personal documents, establishing a chain of custody for evidence in case 31E-MM-108062.

events.title: Property seizure at Epstein's Palm Beach home
events.description: Law enforcement executed a search and seized numerous items from 345 South County Road, Palm Beach, FL, as part of an investigation into Jeffrey Epstein.

locations: 345 SOUTH COUNTY ROAD PALM BEACH FL 33480
keyFacts: On August 28, 2006, law enforcement seized a vast array of items from Jeffrey Epstein's Palm Beach mansion, including multiple massage tables, framed photos of nude girls, vibrators, and numerous videos, CDs, and audio tapes.

The seized evidence includes items suggestive of sexual activity and the grooming of minors, such as 'BLACK FRAMED PHOTO OF NUDE GIRL', 'TWO VIBRATORS', 'BOTTLE OF JOY JELLY', and a 'HIGH SCHOOL TRANSCRIPT - AH'.
The document is a formal FBI property inventory (FD-192) establishing a detailed chain of custody for evidence in case number 31E-MM-108062, indicating a serious federal investigation was underway.

Among the seized materials were surveillance tapes, phone message books, flight information, and documents containing numerous initials (e.g., J.L., A., G., C.W., P.S.), suggesting the investigation involved tracking communications and associates.
The document references items pulled from trash ('TRASH PULL'), indicating law enforcement was also collecting discarded materials from the property.
